The following function computes the maximum value contained in an integer array p[] of size n (n >= 1).
int max(int *p, int n) {
    int a=0, b=n-1;
    while ( __________ ) {
        if (p[a] <= p[b]) { a = a+1; }
        else { b = b-1; }
    }
    return p[a];
}
The missing loop condition is
(A) a != n
(B) b != 0
(C) b > (a + 1)
(D) b != a

